By Chimezie Godfrey The Nigerian Air Force (NAF) has disclosed that the first batch of A-29 Super Tucano aircraft have arrived Kano. In a statement, the Director of Public Relations and Information, Nigerian Air Force, Air Commodore Edward Gabkwet revealed that the aircraft arrived on Thursday at about 12.34pm. According to him, on hand to receive the aircraft were the Minister of Defence, Major General Bashir Magashi (Rtd), Chief of Army Staff, Lieutenant General Faruk Yahaya and Chief of Air Staff, Air Marshal Oladayo Amao.